YAML Header & Document Structure
-	Goal: Create an appropriate YAML header
-	Needs: Quarto, RStudio
-	Steps:
  o	Add a title (Activity 14)
  o	Set the author to be me with my name
  o	Add the date
    	Set date-modified: now to reflect the updating process
  o	Set output information
    	Make sure the margins are 1 inch (number-depth: 5)
    	Set toc to false so there is no table of contents
  o	Make sure the QMD file will render as a pdf
  o	Set cap-location: top so that captions will appear above their figures/tables

Armed Forces Data Wrangling Redux (Activity #08 & #10)
-	Goal: Create a frequency table with a smaller subset of soldiers 
-	Needs: Activity 08 and 10 code, googlesheets4, dplyr, tidyverse, QMD file
-	Steps:
  o	(All inside of a code section in the QMD file)
  o	Load needed packages
  o	Create smaller subset
    	Filter out army and pay grade O ranks
  o	Use tabyl to create a frequency table
    	Use adorn_totals to add a total row
    	Use adorn_percentages to add relative frequencies
    	Use adorn_pct_formatting to set relative frequencies to two decimal places
    	Use adorn_title to add a title
    	Mutate and use across to add commas into the table where numbers need them
  o	Use kable to visualize the frequency table
    	Add a caption “Ranks of US Army Officers by Sex”
    	Style the table with a font size of 16 and adding stripes and condensing the table
  o	Add a paragraph detailing what the frequency table is and what it shows with regards to sex and rank’s relationship in the Army for officers.

