  o	Add a paragraph detailing why I picked the names and what the trends in the graph show with regards to the 4 chosen names

Plotting a Mathematical Function (Activity #03)
-	Goal: Create a function that calculates maximum box volume based on length of side cutout
-	Needs: ggplot2
-	Steps:
  o	Create a function
    	Set length = 36 and width = 48, set x (side cutout length) to be variable
    	Lengthbox = length – 2x
    	Widthbox = width – 2x
    	Heightbox = x
    	Volumebox = lengthbox * widthbox * heightbox
  o	Create a dataframe out of the possible cutout side lengths
    	Trial and error with the graph shows the range should be from 0 to 18 by intervals of 1
  o	Create a plot made with ggplot2
    	Use stat_function to create a line plot using the function
    	Add alt text
    	Add labels and a title
    	Add a theme
    	Make the x scale break in intervals of 1 from 0 to 18
  o	Add a paragraph that describes the line plot and tells what the maximum box volume is and what side length is needed to achieve it.

