Repo Plan
----

Goal: Use branches to good effect
o	Needs: GitHub
o	Steps:
  	Create a dev branch
  	Commit to dev branches
  	Once all commits are done, create a pull request to merge with the main branch
  	Complete the pull request

Goal: Create and solve two issues
o	Needs: GitHub
o	Steps:
  	Create two issues
    •	Issues: Add QMD/PDF, Add plan
    •	Issues have relevant labels/tags applied
  	Tag issues as they are resolved
    •	Close issues

Goal: Create multiple meaningful commits
o	Needs: GitHub
o	Steps:
  	Each commit should actually serve a purpose
  	Each commit has an appropriate summary message
    •	Message describes What and Why without diving into How
  	Pull requests have both title and description of what the request is meant to accomplish

Goal: Create an appropriate README
o	Needs: GitHub, RStudio
o	Steps:
  	Create a README file in RStudio
  	In the readme, put:
    •	What the repo is about
    •	Where the data is from
    •	Current plan for the project
    •	How the repo is organized
    •	Contact information

Goal: Create a plan document
o	Needs: Microsoft Word, RStudio, GitHub
o	Steps:
  	Plan should include both project and repo
  	Should be complete, with goals, needs, and steps
  	Copy plan from word into R file
  	Commit R file to repo

Goal: Have an output file for the repo
o	Needs: Activity 14 QMD, GitHub
o	Steps:
  	Generate a PDF from Activity #14
  	Commit PDF to repo

Goal: Have a QMD file in the repo
o	Needs: Activity 14 QMD, GitHub
o	Steps:
  	Commit Activity 14 QMD file to the repo